p-case" target="_blank">US special counsel obtained search warrant for Trump’s Twitter account</a></h2><div class="description"> The US special counsel who is investigating Donald Trump obtained a search warrant for the former president’s Twitter account. Social media platform delayed complying, court filing shows, prompting judge to hold Twitter in contempt and fine it $350,000. The delay in compliance prompted a federal.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 20:09:12 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/twitter-fined-contempt-trump-case" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/10/rohingya-dead-boat-capsizes-off-coast-of-myanmar" target="_blank">At least 17 people dead after boat carrying Rohingya refugees capsizes off coast of Myanmar</a></h2><div class="description"> Boat carrying Rohingya refugees from Myanmar to Malaysia capsized on Monday. Bodies of 10 women and seven men have been recovered after being washed up on the coast of Myanmar. Eight people who were rescued are being held at a local police station, said Bya Latt.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 12:35:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/10/rohingya-dead-boat-capsizes-off-coast-of-myanmar" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/10/china-moratoriums-on-fishing-do-nothing-to-protect-squid" target="_blank">China’s moratoriums on fishing do ‘nothing to protect squid’</a></h2><div class="description"> Analysis by conservation group Oceana suggests areas where suspension imposed are not fished by fleets anyway. China’s ministry of agriculture and rural affairs announced a pilot program banning fishing in parts of the south-west Atlantic Ocean from July to October and parts of eastern Pacific Ocean from September to December.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 10:53:14 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/10/china-moratoriums-on-fishing-do-nothing-to-protect-squid" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/cyprus-begins-treating-islands-sick-cats-with-anti-covid-pills" target="_blank">Cyprus begins treating island’s sick cats with anti-Covid pills</a></h2><div class="description"> Vets receive medication originally meant for people amid virulent feline coronavirus that has killed thousands of cats. The island’s health ministry began discharging the treatment on 8 August – long celebrated as International Cat Day – in what is hoped will be the beginning of the end of the disease.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/cyprus-begins-treating-islands-sick-cats-with-anti-covid-pills" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/new-orleans-catholic-church-priests-sexual-abuse-protect-children" target="_blank">New Orleans archdiocese failed to monitor priests accused of sexual abuse</a></h2><div class="description"> Victims’ advocates detailed church’s neglect in following oversight recommendations when transferring accused clergy. New Orleans archbishop hid ‘credibly accused’ abusers from public ministry following molestation allegations – but who for years stayed in close proximity to and were financially supported by the church.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 10:00:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/new-orleans-catholic-church-priests-sexual-abuse-protect-children" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/san-francisco-self-driving-car-autonomous-regulation-google-gm" target="_blank">Regulators to decide on around-the-clock robotaxi service in San Francisco</a></h2><div class="description"> Waymo and Cruise have already been operating a small fleet of vehicles without drivers during off-peak hours in the city. Google and GM want the state to allow their self-driving fleets to operate 24/7, but critics say they are ‘not ready for prime time’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 10:00:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/san-francisco-self-driving-car-autonomous-regulation-google-gm" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/us-voices-fears-for-niger-ex-president-who-is-running-out-of-food" target="_blank">US voices fears for Niger’s ex-president, who is ‘running out of food’</a></h2><div class="description"> Mohamed Bazoum, the West African nation’s democratically elected leader, has been held at the presidential palace in Niamey with his wife and son since July 26. His party said he and his family were running out of food and living under increasingly dire conditions.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 05:38:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/us-voices-fears-for-niger-ex-president-who-is-running-out-of-food" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/pak-n-save-savey-meal-bot-ai-app-malfunction-recipes" target="_blank">Supermarket AI meal planner app suggests recipe that would create chlorine gas</a></h2><div class="description"> Pak ‘n’ Save’s Savey Meal-bot cheerfully created unappealing recipes when customers experimented with non-grocery household items. It was advertised as a way for customers to creatively use up leftovers during cost of living crisis. The app asks users to enter in various ingredients in their homes and auto-generates a meal plan.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:19:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/pak-n-save-savey-meal-bot-ai-app-malfunction-recipes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/argentina-election-campaigns-suspended-girl-killed-buenos-aires" target="_blank">Argentina election campaigns suspended after 11-year old killed in robbery</a></h2><div class="description"> Morena Domínguez was attacked by two robbers riding a motorcycle in Lanús, Buenos Aires. The 11-year-old was about to arrive at school early on Wednesday morning in the Buenos Aires district. The attackers snatched her mobile phone, and she fell to the pavement where she was left unconscious.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 21:25:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/argentina-election-campaigns-suspended-girl-killed-buenos-aires" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/kim-jong-un-fires-dismisses-north-korea-top-military-general-pak-su-il" target="_blank">Kim Jong-un fires North Korea’s top general and calls for weapons production boost</a></h2><div class="description"> Leader replaces Pak Su-il with defence minister, Gen Ri Yong-gil, and urges further military drills. Kim Jong-un calls for more preparations for possibility of war, boost in weapons production and expansion of drills. It remains unclear if Ri will retain his role as defence minister.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 00:42:10 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/kim-jong-un-fires-dismisses-north-korea-top-military-general-pak-su-il" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/10/woodhill-britain-failing-prison-system-summerhall-edinburgh" target="_blank">Woodhill review – astonishing portrait of Britain’s failing prison system</a></h2><div class="description"> Matt Woodhead’s urgent drama focuses on the deaths of three real prisoners. Kevin Scarlett, Stephen Farrar and Chris Carpenter, all with severe mental health issues, were each found dead in their cells between 2013 and 2018. Their families have been dogged in their pursuit of answers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 10:17:17 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/10/woodhill-britain-failing-prison-system-summerhall-edinburgh" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/10/la-cage-aux-folles-review-regents-park-open-air-theatre-london" target="_blank">La Cage aux Folles review – dazzling revival is hilarious and heartfelt</a></h2><div class="description"> Harvey Fierstein's witty book still crackles 40 years on from the Broadway premiere. Jerry Herman’s heartfelt score (so pure and romantic) seduces us all. Ryan Dawson Laight's costumes dazzle; one skirt has its own set of wheels. Stephen Mear's choreography is slick but – even better – very funny.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 12:35:19 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/10/la-cage-aux-folles-review-regents-park-open-air-theatre-london" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/paul-mccartney-billy-joel-concerts-front-row-seats" target="_blank">‘Paul McCartney winked right at me’: the fans who buy nosebleed seats – and get whisked to the front</a></h2><div class="description"> Billy Joel has been playing one sold-out concert a month at Madison Square Garden for a decade. Joel said he wouldn't sell tickets to the front row because they were often sold at inflated prices to rich people. He said he'd see them "sitting there puffing on a cigar, ‘entertain me, piano man’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 05:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/10/paul-mccartney-billy-joel-concerts-front-row-seats" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/the-case-against-cosby-review-a-revelatory-story-from-the-woman-who-brought-him-down" target="_blank">The Case Against Cosby review – a revelatory story from the woman who brought him down</a></h2><div class="description"> This powerful film rails against a legal system that so often fails victims of sexual assault. It is a vivid, intimate – and ultimately redemptive – look at trauma. The Case Against Cosby is based on memoir written by Andrea Constand, who is the only woman able to gain a conviction against Cosby.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:00:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/the-case-against-cosby-review-a-revelatory-story-from-the-woman-who-brought-him-down" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/hear-here-gary-lineker-alan-shearer-micah-richards-the-rest-is-football" target="_blank">Best podcasts of the week: Gary Lineker and friends team up for a new football show</a></h2><div class="description"> The Match of the Day presenter joins Alan Shearer and Micah Richards for The Rest Is Football. Simon Kent Fung remembers learning about Alana Chen in 2019: “A girl from Boulder, Colorado, who wanted to become a nun, was told to keep a secret, and who died at 24”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 08:45:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/10/hear-here-gary-lineker-alan-shearer-micah-richards-the-rest-is-football" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2023/aug/10/artists-using-artificial-intelligence-science-gallery" target="_blank">Meet the artists reclaiming AI from big tech – with the help of cats, bees and drag queens</a></h2><div class="description"> AI’s potential is huge and terrifying, but a new generation of artists is starting to find new uses for the technology. For these AI-generated drag kings and queens, life really is a cabaret. Between each song, the performers underwent a kind of metamorphosis, melting down into amorphous masses of pixels and then re-forming.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 07:00:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2023/aug/10/artists-using-artificial-intelligence-science-gallery" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">From Pig Beach to Dunn’s River Falls: 10 must-visit Caribbean destinations – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is home to the world’s best beaches, pretty towns, waterfalls and national parks. There are stunning marine life, the best beaches and pretty towns in the world's most beautiful places. Here's the Caribbean in all its glory, including some pretty towns and waterfalls.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:35:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">From snorkelling to surfing: nine must-try Caribbean beach and water activities</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean offers a huge variety of tempting activities from snorkelling to scuba diving. Windsurfing and waterskiing is a must-try activity for everyone. The Exu Exu is one of the Caribbean’s most beautiful, vividly coloured coral reefs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:38:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Nightlife, loveseats and beautiful beaches: why the Caribbean makes for the perfect romantic holiday</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is an unbeatable destination for a romantic getaway with your loved one. From Jamaica to the hidden gem that is Curaçao, there’s something to suit every couple, whether on honeymoon, celebrating an anniversary, or just escaping everyday life for a taste of luxury.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:37:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Waterfalls, history and the world’s first underwater sculpture park: seven exciting things to do in the Caribbean</a></h2><div class="description"> The islands of the Caribbean are like nowhere else on Earth. From cocktails to coral reefs, they offer something for all tastes and tempos. Enjoy a classic mojito or piña colada on the white sand beaches of Barbados or Jamaica. Explore the area’s rich history and natural beauty.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:36:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/2023/aug/10/how-learning-to-swim-at-60-set-me-free" target="_blank">‘Move forward. Flap around a little!’ How learning to swim at 60 set me free</a></h2><div class="description"> Years of chronic neck and back spasms had stolen all the variety and fun I used to find in working out, especially that amped-up endorphin high. By his early 50s, I had spent thousands of dollars trying to mitigate this pain with alternative treatments. I was told swimming would make me fit and strong-minded, but first I had to navigate the slow lane.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/2023/aug/10/how-learning-to-swim-at-60-set-me-free" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/dream-holiday-at-home-how-i-holidayed-in-venice-without-leaving-york" target="_blank">‘Soaked and shivering, I order a spritz’: how I holidayed in Venice – without leaving York</a></h2><div class="description"> Unable to get to Italy, I spent a day recreating a Venetian mini-break in my home town. Who needs the Grand Canal when you’ve got the Ouse? Thankfully I live in York, which is also very old and full of locals complaining about tourists.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/dream-holiday-at-home-how-i-holidayed-in-venice-without-leaving-york" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/literary-dorset-pj-harvey-thomas-hardy-william-barnes" target="_blank">Of Thomas Hardy and PJ Harvey: on the trail of Dorset’s inspirational powers</a></h2><div class="description"> The county’s people, landscapes and villages have provided material for generations of writers. Thomas Hardy stamped his personality over his idea of Wessex, reviving an ancient kingdom and giving towns and villages new names. Every town seems to have been a film set for a Hardy adaptation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 06:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/10/literary-dorset-pj-harvey-thomas-hardy-william-barnes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/10/council-refused-to-pay-full-cost-of-replacing-two-pothole-damaged-tyres" target="_blank">Council refused to pay full cost of replacing two pothole-damaged tyres</a></h2><div class="description"> Reading borough council admitted breach of duty but deducted 30% from claim. Council insurance does not include ‘betterment’ - replacing old items with new. Unless you can produce receipts showing that the damaged tyres had been bought very recently, the council will deduct a sum from a claim.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 06:00:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/10/council-refused-to-pay-full-cost-of-replacing-two-pothole-damaged-tyres" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/10/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-5-review-a-big-screen-inside-and-out" target="_blank">Samsung Galaxy Z Flip 5 review: a big screen inside and out</a></h2><div class="description"> The new Z Flip 5 costs £1,049 ($999/A$1,649) - £50 more than last year’s model. It comes with twice the starting storage and a collection of small but meaningful upgrades. The new flip phone has a bigger, more useful screen on the outside for its fifth generation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 06:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/10/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-5-review-a-big-screen-inside-and-out" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/hiking-relationships-family-dating" target="_blank">What I learned from hiking with a partner who strode ahead – and wouldn’t slow down</a></h2><div class="description"> In our 20s, we’d trekked for three months in Nepal, only stopping to sip hot chai and eat warm dal for meals. After serving in the Peace Corps in the Central African Republic, I'd anticipated a romantic journey as a couple with my best friend turned boyfriend. But as hiking partners, we were rarely together.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:00:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/hiking-relationships-family-dating" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Why Barcelona’s beaches are disappearing – video</a></h2><div class="description"> In 2010, Barcelona’s nine city beaches were topped up with 700,000 cubic metres of sand. Since then, 70% of that sand has disappeared. In the past 20 years the rate of erosion along Spain's east coast has been accelerating. It is partly to do with storms and rising sea levels but there are other factors at play.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 08:46:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">What you need to know about the 'extreme' heatwave hitting our oceans – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> Sea temperatures, particularly off the north-east coast of England and west of Ireland, are several degrees above normal, breaking records for late spring and early summer. The Met Office has said that according to records dating to 1850, global sea surface temperatures in April and May reached an all-time high.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 14:22:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather and adds a further spurt of warmth to an already overheating world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/10/wilko-shoppers-tell-us-what-you-like-most-about-the-store" target="_blank">Wilko shoppers: tell us what you like most about the store</a></h2><div class="description"> More than 12,000 jobs at risk after Wilko fails to agree a rescue deal. The budget retailer is the largest retailer to collapse into administration since McColl's did. The convenience-store business was rescued by the supermarket Morrisons last year. We’d like to hear from shoppers what they will miss after the news.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 11:31:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/10/wilko-shoppers-tell-us-what-you-like-most-about-the-store" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/people-in-maui-how-have-you-been-affected-by-the-wildfires" target="_blank">People in Maui: how have you been affected by the wildfires?</a></h2><div class="description"> At least 36 people have died in wildfires on the Hawaiian island of Maui. The fires, fanned by strong winds from Hurricane Dora, destroyed businesses in the historic town of Lahaina. There have been 13 evacuations for three fires, and at least two dozen people injured.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 09:15:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/people-in-maui-how-have-you-been-affected-by-the-wildfires" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/10/uk-workers-share-your-experience-of-remote-working" target="_blank">UK workers: share your experience of remote working</a></h2><div class="description"> We want to hear from UK employees who worked remotely during the pandemic about what they’re doing now. Zoom has told employees to come into the office at least twice a week. If you worked remotely, when did you return to in-person working? Or are you still working from home? How do you feel about your situation?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 12:19:07 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/10/uk-workers-share-your-experience-of-remote-working" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/10/summer-picks-are-we-any-closer-to-understanding-long-covid-podcast" target="_blank">Summer picks: are we any closer to understanding long Covid? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Ian Sample hears from Scotland’s Astronomer Royal, Prof Catherine Heymans, about her experience of long Covid and how it has affected her life. He also speaks to Prof Danny Altmann, an immunologist at Imperial College London, about the scientific understanding of the condition.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/10/summer-picks-are-we-any-closer-to-understanding-long-covid-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/audio/2023/aug/10/the-quran-burnings-in-sweden-who-is-fanning-the-flames-podcast" target="_blank">The Qur’an burnings in Sweden: who is fanning the flames? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> The act of burning a holy book in Sweden is not of itself illegal. But a spate of burnings has resulted in outrage at home and abroad – and potentially far-reaching consequences. Sweden is facing diplomatic pressure from the Organisation of Islamic Cooperation, which represents 57 countries. At the same time it is fretting over the support of Turkey to allow it to become a full Nato member.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 02:00:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/audio/2023/aug/10/the-quran-burnings-in-sweden-who-is-fanning-the-flames-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/09/why-the-rest-of-the-world-cant-afford-to-ignore-the-coup-in-niger-podcast" target="_blank">Why the rest of the world can’t afford to ignore the coup in Niger – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> The Sahel region, sometimes called Africa’s ‘coup belt’ has just seen another government ousted. The eighth overthrow of a government in the region in the past three years and may be the most significant. Peter Beaumont and Nesrine Malik on what it means for African – and global – security.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 02:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/09/why-the-rest-of-the-world-cant-afford-to-ignore-the-coup-in-niger-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/08/colombia-set-up-quarter-final-with-england-womens-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">Colombia set up quarter-final with England – Women’s Football Weekly</a></h2><div class="description"> Colombia beat Jamaica 1-0 to reach their first ever quarter-final, where they will face England. Faye Carruthers is joined by Suzy Wrack, Sophie Downey and Jonathan Liew as the round of 16 comes to a close. We also bid farewell to the Reggae Girlz, who became the first Caribbean nation to play in knockout stages of a World Cup, male or female, since Cuba in 1938.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:47:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/08/colombia-set-up-quarter-final-with-england-womens-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/08/the-legacy-of-sinead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">The legacy of Sinéad O’Connor – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Kathryn Ferguson and journalist Simon Hattenstone share their memories of Sinéad O'Connor. Ferguson directed Nothing Compares, a 2022 documentary about the singer's life. She explains why O’Connor spoke out about abuse in the Catholic church in the early 1990s when it was still taboo to do so.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 02:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/08/the-legacy-of-sinead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/10/our-history-is-rotting-away-the-newspaper-archivists-preserving-nigerias-past" target="_blank">‘Our history is rotting away’: the newspaper archivists preserving Nigeria’s past</a></h2><div class="description"> PM News was founded in 1994 but stopped printing physical copies in 2015. Project will be Nigeria’s first interactive digital newspaper archive. More than 50,000 pages of PM News will be saved for posterity by an ambitious archive project. The project is based in Lekki, an affluent suburb of Lagos, Nigeria.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 05:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/10/our-history-is-rotting-away-the-newspaper-archivists-preserving-nigerias-past" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/ohio-election-issue-1-republicans-abortion-vote" target="_blank">Ohio Republicans bet voters would dilute their own power. They lost</a></h2><div class="description"> Referendum shows concerns over abortion access remain a powerful force in American politics. Republicans bet that turnout would be low in an election held in the middle of the summer (it was just 8% in last year's August contest) They bet that voters in the state, which voted for Donald Trump in 2016 and 2020, would willingly dilute their own political power.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 10:00:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/ohio-election-issue-1-republicans-abortion-vote" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/2023/aug/10/make-mud-not-war-us-weather-warfare-vietnam-commando-lava-ho-chi-minh" target="_blank">‘Make mud, not war’: how US used weather warfare in Vietnam</a></h2><div class="description"> Top-secret project Commando Lava caused disruption along strategically vital Ho Chi Minh trail. US military weaponised this effect in an attempt to halt traffic on the strategically vital trail. The project had Hercules transport aircraft flying at low level to disperse powder engineered to turn mud into glutinous super-mud.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 05:00:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/2023/aug/10/make-mud-not-war-us-weather-warfare-vietnam-commando-lava-ho-chi-minh" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-